column4: Hey, I'm having a problem with Synaptic, can someone help me please?
None of the packages are showing up at all.
I can paste the error message if needed.
Anyone? It should be a pretty quick fix, just adding something in a file somewhere, but I have no idea how.
Still have the same error message.

E: The package virtualbox needs to be reinstalled, but I can't find an archive for it.
2007-09-14T10:42:00.000Z	Oswy		E: Internal error opening cache (1). Please report.
Looks like you'll have to download the virtualbox deb again and reinstall it.
How did you install it the first time?
Do you use it?
What I'm asking is, do you want to keep it or get rid of it? :P
I'd recommend "aptitude remove virtualbox" then "aptitude update" and "aptitude upgrade"

E: I wasn't able to locate a file for the virtualbox package. This might mean you need to manually fix this package. (due to missing arch)
2007-09-14T10:51:00.000Z	Viaken	Oswy	You'll have to sudo all those, sorry, but that doesn't look like it's going to work... How about dpkg -r virtualbox"?
Have you changed your repos recently?
Let me poke around a bit here.
Don't suppose you know what version it was?
Nope, sorry.
The site says 1.5.0 is current. 1.4.0 seems to be in the repos? Try going to http://virtualbox.org/wiki/Downloads and downloading the "Fiesty Fawn" deb and reinstalling it.
Hmm, how do I open a program as root?
gksudo VBox I think
Oh, if you haven't installed the deb, you'll need to "sudo dpkg -i debname.deb"
k, it's installed.
